THE trending rumour that Platinum Stars have been sold to a consortium comprising businessmen from Cape Town, which could include head coach Roger de Sa according to some reports, seems to have left a bitter taste in the mouths of Dikwena players.Players put on brave faces on Saturday when they lost 2-0 to Orlando Pirates at the Royal Bafokeng Stadium after goals by Justin Shonga and Thembinkosi Lorch. But their angry and heartbroken captain, Vuyo Mere, came out guns blazing after their Absa Premiership clash, blaming the players for their slump, not the rumoured sale of the club. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvHMxkcJ1tghr1hMlNIbhhqd6wNN2ORwZCFlyD9O0SQ9ViB_mKdvdkBV5PntI6IjYqumwsf4DHVqBgOxA-ZHaWYfvJ9llWOaoUMPMUNxZDPv3Wrx3cglCz2KLly958tmRqHZb1erY6a9C0S__R7MgFnEcRdFGcSc-2GCPsNsubuwrzycElnsI-Bn8qxBimC0bmOqEHctXLOz1Tl6loghAMM5xriwHiWpP5qXTMXWSXd1A2bjinseB0OTieGnh-ekIOHnu4XY2BufCo6YnbARv-3zA\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzGD56SnpMlMlEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
